00:01:41.800 --> 00:01:43.110
You're the one

00:01:43.110 --> 00:01:44.440
who makes decisions.

00:01:46.720 --> 00:01:47.560
What?

00:01:49.900 --> 00:01:50.580
Well.

00:01:50.700 --> 00:01:51.500
Why are you

00:01:51.620 --> 00:01:52.780
suddenly quiet when I ask?

00:01:53.020 --> 00:01:54.820
No, I'm not avoiding anything.

00:01:54.820 --> 00:01:57.180
I'm just... Thinking.

00:01:57.180 --> 00:01:57.780
Well...

00:01:57.900 --> 00:01:59.820
Here's what I think.

00:01:59.820 --> 00:02:02.980
Tell Bichen

00:02:02.980 --> 00:02:03.980
to go talk

00:02:03.980 --> 00:02:06.740
to her parents first.

00:02:07.180 --> 00:02:09.820
See what requests they have.

00:02:09.820 --> 00:02:11.580
Then we'll know where we stand.

00:02:11.580 --> 00:02:13.820
Right? If we meet them unprepared

00:02:13.820 --> 00:02:15.660
and we can't agree on anything,

00:02:16.260 --> 00:02:17.140
then

00:02:17.460 --> 00:02:19.180
there's no room to negotiate.

00:02:19.740 --> 00:02:20.580
Right?

00:02:21.220 --> 00:02:22.340
That makes sense.

00:02:22.660 --> 00:02:23.580
I'll talk to Bichen.

00:02:24.060 --> 00:02:24.900
Good.

00:02:26.020 --> 00:02:26.340
Xiang.

00:02:26.340 --> 00:02:26.860
What?

00:02:26.860 --> 00:02:27.820
Listen.

00:02:27.820 --> 00:02:28.660
What's wrong?

00:02:30.220 --> 00:02:31.940
What's with all the waving? Enough.

00:02:32.460 --> 00:02:33.460
Have more.

00:02:33.980 --> 00:02:36.020
What requests do we have?

00:02:37.460 --> 00:02:38.300
Bichen,

00:02:39.380 --> 00:02:41.460
did Xu Zhidong ask you to feel us out?

00:02:41.820 --> 00:02:43.380
How can you call it that?

00:02:44.060 --> 00:02:45.840
Getting married
isn't a business negotiation.

00:02:46.980 --> 00:02:48.420
Two families becoming one.

00:02:48.900 --> 00:02:50.540
That's basically
like starting a company.

00:02:53.220 --> 00:02:54.060
Chen,

00:02:54.300 --> 00:02:55.740
our only request is

00:02:56.700 --> 00:02:58.740
that Zhidong treats you well.

00:02:59.980 --> 00:03:02.060
That's the same as having no request.

00:03:02.380 --> 00:03:03.500
Sometimes a single "well"

00:03:03.500 --> 00:03:05.260
can weigh a ton,

00:03:05.500 --> 00:03:07.420
sometimes it feels lighter
than a feather.

00:03:07.940 --> 00:03:09.560
If he treats you well today,

00:03:09.560 --> 00:03:11.300
what if he stops treating
you well tomorrow?

00:03:11.300 --> 00:03:12.380
Mom, I know him.

00:03:12.380 --> 00:03:13.580
He won't.

00:03:15.940 --> 00:03:16.780
Bichen,

00:03:17.500 --> 00:03:20.140
do you know why marriage is called
an important life event?

00:03:20.420 --> 00:03:21.500
Because it turns

00:03:21.940 --> 00:03:24.340
two people with no blood relation

00:03:24.340 --> 00:03:26.100
into immediate family.

00:03:26.620 --> 00:03:28.700
You're binding your lives together.

00:03:28.900 --> 00:03:30.420
Isn't that difficult?

00:03:31.180 --> 00:03:31.820
It is.

00:03:31.940 --> 00:03:33.140
Exactly because it's difficult,

00:03:33.620 --> 00:03:35.420
that's why weddings are made big.

00:03:35.980 --> 00:03:37.100
Once you're married,

00:03:37.100 --> 00:03:38.980
both families pour in all they've got.

00:03:38.980 --> 00:03:40.470
The bride and groom both take the plunge

00:03:40.480 --> 00:03:42.520
